# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [0.0.1] - 2025-12-24

### Added
- Initial project setup with Flask application factory pattern
- Complete RBAC authorization service architecture
- Access control endpoints (`/check-access`, `/batch-check-access`)
- RBAC management endpoints (Roles, Policies, Permissions, User Roles)
- Audit trail system for access logs
- Bootstrap endpoint for tenant initialization
- Health and readiness endpoints for Kubernetes
- Metrics endpoint for Prometheus monitoring
- JWT authentication and authorization middleware
- Rate limiting with Flask-Limiter
- Redis caching support (optional)
- PostgreSQL and SQLite database support
- Identity service client integration
- Comprehensive test suite (unit + integration)
- Docker and Docker Compose configuration
- CI/CD ready with GitHub Actions support
- Code quality tools (Black, Ruff, MyPy, Bandit)
- Pre-commit hooks configuration
- OpenAPI 3.0 specification
- Grafana + Prometheus monitoring stack
- Complete documentation (API, monitoring, testing)
- Dual licensing (AGPLv3 + Commercial)
- Makefile with development commands

### Configuration
- Multi-environment support (development, testing, integration, staging, production)
- Environment-based configuration via `.env` files
- Configurable logging with structured output
- CORS configuration for cross-origin requests
- Database migration support with Alembic

### Documentation
- README with quick start guide
- OpenAPI specification for all endpoints
- Monitoring and metrics documentation
- Testing documentation (unit and integration)
- Coding standards guide
- Contributing guidelines
- Code of conduct

[0.0.1]: https://github.com/waterfall-project/wfp-guardian/releases/tag/v0.0.1
